==Finnish==
===Noun===

''(vulgar)'' hevon[[vittu]] (plural ''hevonvitut'', genitive ''hevonvitun''). Literally "horse's cunt".

# (expletive) bullshit, hell, fuck, devil. 
# (intensifier, in genitive case) fucking, shitty, damned

Sometimes written with space, ''hevon vittu''

Finnish synonyms: hevon[[paska]], hevon[[perse]], hevon[[helvetti]]

===Examples===

# ''Ei tästä tule hevonvittua!'' This just won't fuckin' work out!
# ''Sun kanssas aika ja vaiva menee hevonvittuun!'' With you, I'm giving my time and effort for fucking shit!
# ''Toi hevonvitun ääliö saa kohta turpiin!'' That fucking moron is gonna get beaten!
# ''Missä hevonvitun hornantuutissa sä oikein asut?'' Where in the fucking hell do you live?

===Usage notes===

''Hevonvittu'' means literally "horse's cunt" and it is a corrupt of ''hevosen vittu''. The complete form of the phrase is not used, not even by veterinarians, who might technically use it about a female horse's genitalia. 

